aprika sauce","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 - 300 g basmati rice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1000 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g fresh green beans, tops and tails removed"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"150 g pumpkin flesh, cut into thin slices (5 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 zucchinis (approx. 200 g), cut into thin slices (5 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 carrots (approx. 150 g), cut into thin rounds (5 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"600 - 700 g skinless chicken breast fillets, cut into slices (2 cm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 pinches herb salt, to taste"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp garlic powder"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 ½ - 2 tsp smoked paprika"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tbsp ghee"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"60 g raw cashews"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 tsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"sea salt, for seasoning"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"freshly ground pepper, for seasoning"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1782 kJ \/ 424 kcal","32.7 g","46.6 g","10.7 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the Chicken stock paste with Vegetable stock paste, if preferred. Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the stock paste recipes.","You can replace the ghee with butter.","Washing rice quickly before cooking ensures the rice is wet before cooking, which helps ensure even cooking.","You can use any mix of vegetables you like in this recipe, just ensure they are cut into small pieces (larger pieces will take longer to cook, which could affect the texture of your chicken and rice).","<b>Nut free sauce<b>: When making the sauce, replace cashews and reserved cooking liquid with 250 g coconut cream and cook<b> 1 min\/90°C\/speed 4.<b> Season to taste."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","6 portions"]}